They had an EP out by 2009, and their debut album, "Tourist History," was released in early 2010. It was followed by "Beacon" in August 2012, and by July 2013 the band had already begun work on their third studio album., 1716=Heralded for its live shows, Two Door Cinema Club kicked off a full UK tour in 2013 that started in Belfast on January 18 and wrapped at London's Brixton Academy. Held annually in the United Kingdom, the festival takes place at two parks simultaneously and… Two Door Cinema Club's 2013 UK Tour Plans November 21, 2012 News Heralded for its live shows, Two Door Cinema Club kicked off a full UK tour in 2013 that started in Belfast on January 18 and wrapped at London's Brixton Academy. The band was supported by Bastille and Swim Deep on that trek. It later commenced a three week European tour in Zurich, Switzerland, with support from Dog Is Dead and The 1975, followed by a huge London show at Alexandra Palace on April 27. They finally went on a run of summer festivals, including Scotland's T in the Park, England's Virgin Media V Festival, Portugal's Optimus Alive and their fourth appearance at Glastonbury.
